# D12_GDSC2_INVARIANCE_TEST_v1
# Pre-registration: Measurement Geometry Invariance Test
# Date: 2026-06-07
# Status: PRE-REGISTERED — do not open GDSC2 dose-response data before this commit

## Scientific Purpose

This is NOT a validation experiment. It is a **measurement geometry invariance test**.

PRISM measures log-fold-change (LFC) at a single fixed drug concentration.
GDSC2 measures IC50 and AUC across a multi-point dose-response curve (typically
8 concentrations). These are different cuts of the dose-response relationship.

Invariance claim: if structural z_dr predictions reflect genuine network
pharmacology, the cancer-type sensitivity ranking should persist regardless of
whether drug response is measured as PRISM LFC (single concentration) or
GDSC2 IC50 (dose-curve derived).

Replication = structural signal is geometry-independent (evidence of real mechanism).
No replication = PRISM-specific signal (also informative: signal may be at
assay-concentration, not captured at IC50; or cell line panel differs systematically).

## Structural Basis (from D7 z_dr atlas and D8-D11 results)

All z_dr values from D7_Z_DR_ATLAS_v1 (pre-reg 9dc1b1d).

MEK1 structural positions:
- BRAF-MEL: robust ANCHOR (z1=-1.104, z2=-1.451)
- CRC: robust DAMPER (z1=+1.863, z2=+1.008)
- KRAS-NSCLC: near-zero
- GBM: near-zero

MDM2 structural positions:
- PDAC: robust DAMPER (z1=+1.010, z2=+1.085) — but TP53 mutant ~70%
- BRAF-MEL: DAMPER (delta_r=+0.134)
- EGFR-NSCLC: near-zero

PI3K structural positions:
- CRC: robust ANCHOR (z1=-3.032, z2=-1.872) — direct KRAS->PI3K co-pathway
- BRAF-MEL: robust ANCHOR (z1=-3.032, z2=-2.451) — yet PI3K inhibitors kill CRC more per D9 H2

CDK4/6 (control):
- PDAC: SIGNIFICANT DAMPER (z1=+1.010) but FM1 (no co-pathway confirmed D8 H3)
- No structural basis for PDAC-specific CDK4/6 sensitivity

## Hypotheses

### H1 (MEK inhibitor regime-switch — geometry invariance of D8/D9 signal)

Structural prediction: MEK inhibitors kill BRAF-MEL significantly more than CRC.
PRISM result: d=-0.186 (D8), MEK regime-switch largest in dataset (D9 d=-0.620 vs GBM).

GDSC2 prediction: BRAF-MEL has LOWER IC50 for MEK inhibitors than CRC.
(Lower IC50 = more drug-sensitive = consistent with PRISM LFC signal)

Drugs to test: trametinib, selumetinib, cobimetinib, binimetinib (MEK162)
Cell line filter: melanoma lines with BRAF V600E annotation vs colorectal lines
Pre-registered direction: BRAF-MEL IC50 < CRC IC50 (Mann-Whitney one-sided p<0.05)

H1 CONFIRMED if: BRAF-MEL significantly lower IC50 for ≥1 MEK inhibitor (p<0.05)
H1 DENIED if: no significant difference in IC50 across cancer types

### H2 (MDM2 inhibitor in BRAF-MEL vs NSCLC — geometry invariance of D11 H2)

PRISM result: idasanutlin d=-0.354, p<10^-10 (BRAF-MEL kills more than NSCLC, D11 H2).
Mechanism: synthetic-lethality alignment (CDKN2A loss + MAPK hyperactivation +
intact apoptotic execution machinery).

GDSC2 prediction: BRAF-MEL has LOWER IC50 for nutlin-3 (or other MDM2i in GDSC2)
than lung/NSCLC cancer lines.

Drugs to test: nutlin-3, nutlin-3a, RG7112, idasanutlin (availability determined post-commit)
Pre-registered direction: BRAF-MEL IC50 < NSCLC IC50 (p<0.05)
Pre-registered confound: if MDM2i not in GDSC2 → H2 is UNTESTABLE (not denied)

H2 CONFIRMED if: significant lower IC50 in BRAF-MEL
H2 UNTESTABLE if: no MDM2 inhibitor found in GDSC2 drug list

### H3 (PI3K inhibitor in CRC vs MEL — geometry invariance of D9 H2)

PRISM result: PI3K inhibitors kill CRC significantly more than BRAF-MEL
(D9 H2: p=0.00073, d=+0.390, CRC mean -0.389 vs BRAF-MEL mean -0.334 but CRC less variable).

GDSC2 prediction: CRC has LOWER IC50 for PI3K inhibitors than BRAF-MEL.
Drugs to test: buparlisib (BKM120), alpelisib (BYL719), copanlisib, pictilisib (GDC-0941)
Pre-registered direction: CRC IC50 < BRAF-MEL IC50 (p<0.05)

H3 CONFIRMED if: CRC significantly lower IC50 for ≥1 PI3K inhibitor
H3 DENIED if: no significant difference

### H4 (CDK4/6 inhibitors — null control, FM1)

PRISM result: CDK4/6 inhibitors show no PDAC-specific sensitivity (D8 H3 NOT SUPPORTED,
FM1 = no co-pathway). CDK4/6 is cytostatic — excluded from drug panels — but its
null result is a pre-registered control.

GDSC2 prediction: palbociclib, ribociclib, abemaciclib show NO significant difference
between PDAC and CRC (structural basis absent per D8 pre-reg).

H4 CONFIRMED (null) if: p≥0.05 for PDAC vs CRC CDK4/6 IC50
H4 VIOLATED if: significant PDAC-CRC difference (would require explanation)

## Decision Rule (pre-registered)

| Outcome | Interpretation |
|---------|----------------|
| ≥3/4 H confirmed | Structural signal is measurement-geometry invariant |
| 2/4 confirmed | Partial invariance — some predictions assay-specific |
| ≤1/4 confirmed (H1 included) | PRISM-specific signal; GDSC2 captures different pharmacological geometry |
| H1 denied + H2 denied | MEK and MDM2 signals are PRISM-specific (concentration-dependent) |
| H4 violated | CDK4/6 null result failed — investigate FM1 boundary condition |

## Key pre-registered methodological choices

- IC50 used (not AUC) as primary metric — IC50 is more interpretable for cancer-type comparisons
- GDSC2 v2 (Oct 2023 release: GDSC2_fitted_dose_response_27Oct23.xlsx) is the primary dataset
- Cancer type annotation from GDSC2 TCGA classification column
- Minimum n=5 cell lines per cancer type per drug (for statistical validity)
- Mann-Whitney U (one-sided) as primary test, Cohen's d as effect size
- Drug matching: match on DRUG_NAME column (case-insensitive), not drug ID
- BRAF-mutant melanoma filter: GDSC2 TCGA label 'SKCM' + BRAF_status if available, else all melanoma
- CDK4/6 exclusion from H1-H3 panels (cytostatic confound — pre-established exclusion from D8)
- BET/JQ1 exclusion (potency gap confound — pre-established from D5)

## PRISM-GDSC2 comparison framework (pre-registered analytic interpretation)

PRISM measures: log(treated/untreated) at single fixed concentration (varying by drug)
GDSC2 measures: fitted IC50 from sigmoid dose-response curve (8 concentrations)

If signal persists: structural predictions operate at the pharmacological mechanism level,
not at the specific concentration tested. This strengthens the causal claim.

If signal does not persist: two interpretations (both informative):
(A) The PRISM signal was concentration-dependent (detectable only above a threshold
    that GDSC2 may not reach for all cancer types)
(B) Cell line panel differences (GDSC2 is largely European lines, PRISM is US-based
    Broad Institute lines) cause different clonal composition → different response

Both interpretations reduce confidence differently. (A) = drug sensitivity is
structurally-explained but context-dependent. (B) = cell-line-panel confound.

